# Summary

- Node.js ek **JavaScript runtime environment** hai jo JavaScript ko browser ke bahar run karne deta hai.
- Pehle JavaScript sirf browser me chalti thi, but Node.js ke baad JS se backend/server bhi ban sakta hai.
- Node.js ka main feature hai:
  - **Asynchronous**
  - **Event-driven**
- Iska matlab:
  - multiple tasks ek saath efficiently handle hote hain
  - server fast aur scalable banta hai
- Node.js file system access, network requests, HTTP server creation jaise kaam kar sakta hai.
- Callback functions aur event loop Node ka core concept hai.
- Example diya gaya hai ek simple server ka jo browser me `"Hello World"` bhejta hai.

---

# Asaan Bhasha Me 

## 1. Node.js hota kya hai?

Simple:

> "JavaScript ko browser ke bahar chalane ka engine"

Pehle JS sirf websites ke buttons, animations, forms etc handle karti thi.

Jaise:
- button click
