# Pehle Function Samajh

## Normal Function

```js
function greet(name) {
   console.log("Hello " + name);
}
```

### Breakdown

| Part | Meaning |
|---|---|
| function | function bana rahe |
| greet | function ka naam |
| name | parameter |
| body | actual kaam |

---

# Function Call

```js
greet("Sam");
```

Output:

```text
Hello Sam
```

---

# Anonymous Function

Anonymous = bina naam wala function

```js
const greet = function(name) {
   console.log(name);
}
```

Yahaan:
- function ka khud ka naam nahi hai
- variable `greet` me store hai

---

# Arrow Function

Short syntax version.

```js
const greet = (name) => {
   console.log(name);
}
```

Aur short:

```js
const greet = name => console.log(name);
```

---

# IMPORTANT 🔥

Ye teenon SAME kaam karte hain:

```js
function greet(name) {}
```

```js
const greet = function(name) {}
```

```js
const greet = (name) => {}
```

Bas syntax different hai.

