# CALLBACK ACTUALLY KYA HAI?

## Ye normal callback hai:

```js
function doSomething(callback) {
   callback();
}
```

Yahaan:
- `callback` ek function hai
- doosra function usko run karega

---

# Example

```js
function sayHello() {
   console.log("hello");
}

doSomething(sayHello);
```

Yahaan:
- humne function pass kiya
- call nahi kiya

---

# VERY IMPORTANT ⚠️

## Difference

### ❌ Wrong

```js
doSomething(sayHello());
```

Isme:
- function turant run ho jayega

---

### ✅ Correct

```js
doSomething(sayHello);
```

Isme:
- sirf reference pass hua
- baad me run hoga

---

# forEach Callback

## Ye dekho:

```js
notes.forEach((note) => console.log(note));
```

forEach internally har item pe callback chala raha hai.

Internally kuch aisa hota hai:

```js
for every item:
   callback(item)
```

---

# Under The Hood

Article ka MOST IMPORTANT PART 🔥

```js
function myForEach(array, callback) {
   for(let i=0; i<array.length; i++) {
      callback(array[i]);
   }
}
```

Matlab:

- loop chal raha
- har item callback ko bhej raha

---

# Ye `item` kaha se aaya? 🤡

```js
(item) => console.log(item + 2)
```

`item` callback ko automatically mil raha hai from:

```js
callback(array[i])
```

Matlab:
- `array[i]` pass hua
- woh `item` ban gaya

---

# map Callback

## map kya karta hai?

Purane array ko transform karta hai.

```js
const arr = [1,2,3];

const newArr = arr.map(num => num + 2);
```

Output:

```text
[3,4,5]
```

---

# Internally map kya karta?

```js
for every item:
   result = callback(item)
   newArray.push(result)
```

---

# Event Listener Callback

## MOST REAL WORLD EXAMPLE

```js
element.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
   console.log(event.target.value);
});
```

---

# Isme kya ho raha?

Browser bol raha:

```text
"Jab click hoga tab ye callback chalaunga"
```

---

# `event` kaha se aaya?

Browser khud pass karta hai callback me.

Internally kuch aisa:

```js
callback(eventObject)
```

---

# Callback Ka Golden Rule 🏆

```text
Callbacks ko hum nahi chalate.

Dusra function callback ko chalata hai.
```

---

# First Class Citizens Meaning

JavaScript me functions:
- variable me store ho sakte
- pass ho sakte
- return ho sakte

Isi wajah se callbacks possible hain.

