# PART 3 — Environment Variables

# Summary

- Environment variables = external configurable values.
- Different environments me different values ho sakti hain.
- Secrets store karne ke liye use hote:
  - API keys
  - DB passwords
  - URLs
- `.env` file me store karte hain.
- Access:
```js
process.env
```

---

# Asaan Bhasha Me

## Problem

Suppose:

```js
const password = "sam123";
```

Agar GitHub pe push kar diya:
💀 password leak.

---

# Solution → Environment Variables

Sensitive cheeze code ke bahar rakho.

---

# `.env` File

```env
DB_PASSWORD=sam123
API_KEY=xyz
```

---

# Access Kaise Kare?

```js
process.env.DB_PASSWORD
```

---

# Real Meaning

```text
"Code ke bahar values rakho taaki environment ke according change ho sake."
```

---

# Environment Kya Hota?

| Environment | Meaning |
|---|---|
| Development | local machine |
| Production | deployed app |
| Testing | test server |

---

# Example

Development DB:
```text
localhost database
```

Production DB:
```text
real production database
```

Same code.
Different environment variables.

---

# NODE_ENV

Industry standard variable.

Example:

```env
NODE_ENV=development
```

or

```env
NODE_ENV=production
```

---

# Code Example

```js
if(process.env.NODE_ENV === "production") {
   console.log("Production mode");
}
```

---

# Running With Env Variables

## Directly

```bash
NODE_ENV=prod node index.js
```

---

# export Command

```bash
export NODE_ENV=prod
```

Current shell session ke liye variable set.

---

# `.env` Best Method

```env
NODE_ENV=prod
VIDEO_URL=https://youtube.com
```

Run:

```bash
node --env-file=.env index.js
```

---

# MOST IMPORTANT ⚠️

## NEVER PUSH `.env`

Add to:

```text
.gitignore
```

warna:
- passwords leak
- API keys leak
- database hacked

💀💀💀

---

# Why Environment Variables OP Hain 🔥

## Benefits

| Benefit | Why |
|---|---|
| Security | secrets hidden |
| Flexibility | env-specific configs |
| Cleaner code | hardcoding nahi |
| Deployment friendly | prod/dev separate |

---

# Important Point

Environment variables ALWAYS:

```text
STRING
```

hoti hain.

---

# Example

```env
PORT=3000
```

Actually:
```text
"3000"
```

string hai.

---

# Conversion Example

```js
Number(process.env.PORT)
```

---

# `.env.sample`

Industry practice:

```env
DB_URL=
API_KEY=
JWT_SECRET=
```

Taaki dusre devs ko pata chale:
➡ kya variables chahiye.

---

# FULL Mental Model 🧠

```text
.env file
    ↓
Node loads values
    ↓
process.env object
    ↓
Code uses them
```

---

